<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="65b637b3-853b-50be-93c7-b3b338bdfc24" activityNameId="b6f41598-3a19-4ec8-baec-a60744070278" parentActivityId="48f85f3e-a31f-43b2-948d-0bf57666097a" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1" energyValues="0">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">transport, passenger train</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The dataset starts with the production of a long-distance train.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The dataset ends with the service of transporting 1 passenger over a distance of 1 km by a long-distance train. The dataset includes the production, the maintenance and the energy use and operation emissions of a long-distance train, the construction of a railway track. The inventory of the energy use and operation emissions includes the actual energy consumption  (11000 t Diesel and 1121 GWh of electricity) due to traction of passenger trains.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The dataset represents the entire transport life cycle of a passenger train in Belgium. Data of the energy use and operation emissions for the operation of average trains in Belgium (regional trains, S-Bahn, long distance-trains), the data has been determined top down by International Rail Statistics. Particulate emissions due to abrasion of rail tracks, wheels, brakes and overhead contact line is included according to Swiss situation. Emission of sulphur hexafluoride (SF6) occurring during conversion at traction substations are accounted for.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="6709702f-062f-411b-9d54-baadfdd62383">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">4911:Passenger rail transport, interurban</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <classification classificationId="88f07788-20eb-4488-ae28-7f1330622531">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">EcoSpold01Categories</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">transport systems/train</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="0ff33cbc-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">BE</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Data of energy use and operation emissions refers to average transport conditions</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Demand factors of various transport components required to fulfill the functional unit of one pkm. In order to account for the fact that the same rail tracks are used for both passenger and goods transportation are applied allocation factors. For the energy use and operation emissions data, all technologies are included, the train is operated with the country electricity mix.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2000-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">For the energy use and operation emissions data, all data is based on situation in the year 2000, except the specific energy consumption per pkm (year 2007)</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
